# IBM CLG Custom Agents — Project Conventions

## Design System

This site follows IBM's **Carbon Design System** aligned with watsonx Orchestrate.

- **Border radius**: Always `0` on interactive elements (buttons, inputs, modals, cards, badges containers)
- **Header**: Dark sticky header (`--header-bg: #161616`) with format: `Title | powered by IBM watsonx Orchestrate [BADGE]`
- **Page background**: `var(--bg-page)` (`#f4f4f4`)
- **Card hover effects**: Preserve existing card styling — do not modify

## CSS Variables (defined in `style.css`)

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--ibm-blue` | `#0f62fe` | Primary actions, links |
| `--vendor-blue` | `#0066CC` | Vendor card accents |
| `--text-primary` | `#161616` | Headings, body text |
| `--text-secondary` | `#525252` | Subheadings, labels |
| `--text-helper` | `#6f6f6f` | Helper/muted text |
| `--header-bg` | `#161616` | Dark header |
| `--bg-page` | `#f4f4f4` | Page background |

Badge color: IBM Blue 50 (`#4589ff`)

## Font Weights (IBM Plex Sans)

| Weight | Usage |
|--------|-------|
| 100 (Thin) | "powered by" in header |
| 400 (Regular) | Body text, titles |
| 600 (Semi-Bold) | Buttons, labels |
| 700 (Bold) | "IBM" branding text |

## File Naming

- Agent pages: `agent-{category}-{type}-{paper}.html` (e.g., `agent-procurement-mpa-redhat.html`)
- All agent pages share one `wxOConfiguration` pattern with unique `agentId` and `agentEnvironmentId`

## Commit Style

- Small, focused commits with descriptive messages
- Use HEREDOC format for multi-line commit messages
- Always push after committing

## Key Behaviors

- The "Last updated" date in index.html auto-updates via `document.lastModified` — never hardcode it
- Productivity Gains Calculator data auto-saves to `localStorage` (key: `clg_calculator_data`)
- Welcome modal shows once per browser session (`sessionStorage`)
- Admin page mirrors main page header (only badge text differs)

## Documentation Sync

When adding, removing, or modifying rules or skills in `.cursor/`, update the following to reflect the change:
- The **"Cursor AI Integration"** section in `README.md` (including the summary table)
- The **file structure tree** in `README.md`
- The **"Cursor AI Integration"** section in `SETUP.md`
